0 Pârtha, when a man is satisfied in the Self by Self alone and has completely
cast out all desires from the mind, then he is said to be of steady wisdom. ...

When he completely withdraws his senses from sense-objects as the tortoise
withdraws its limbs, then his wisdom becomes well-established.
